"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750870","Home Office","false","2017-07-17","<p>Responding to 101 calls is an operational matter for policing. The Home Office no longer collects 101 data, but you can find the published data at <a href="https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/policeuk/call-handling/101_call_handling_Jun_2014.zip" target="_blank">https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/policeuk/call-handling/101_call_handling_Jun_2014.zip</a></p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","4264 ; 4269 ; 4401 ; 4403 ; 4404","2017-07-17T16:44:21.777Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750870/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750870/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750870/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-11","101 Calls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the average time taken was to answer a call to the Police 101 number in the most recent period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","4405"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750871","Home Office","false","2017-07-17","<p>Responding to 101 calls is an operational matter for policing. The Home Office no longer collects 101 data, but you can find the published data at <a href="https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/policeuk/call-handling/101_call_handling_Jun_2014.zip" target="_blank">https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/policeuk/call-handling/101_call_handling_Jun_2014.zip</a></p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","4264 ; 4269 ; 4401 ; 4404 ; 4405","2017-07-17T16:44:21.537Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750871/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750871/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750871/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-11","101 Calls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many Police 101 call centres have been (a) closed and (b) merged since 7 May 2015.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","4403"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750872","Department of Health","false","2017-07-17","<p>As part of the response to the tragic events at Grenfell Tower, actions have been implemented across the National Health Service to assess the risks of similar issues and ensure that the NHS estate is safe. The process of checking and testing the NHS’s estate is continuing.</p><p>Fire safety checks of NHS facilities are regularly undertaken in line with legislation and guidance. Hospitals are well prepared – each one has a tailored fire safety plan, which includes assessment of the provision of fire safety precautions including alarms and evacuation plans. But nothing is more important than the safety of patients and staff, so on a precautionary basis we asked all hospitals to conduct additional checks. Jim Mackey, Chief Executive of NHS Improvement instigated inspections by local fire and rescue services on 24 June 2017. All NHS trusts and foundation trusts were asked to carry out urgent fire safety checks following the Grenfell Tower fire. All NHS trusts have provided assurance that they have undertaken a fire risk assessment in the past 12 months.</p><p>As of 7 July, six trusts had been identified with buildings with aluminium composite material cladding, and they have therefore initiated additional fire safety precautions.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-07-17T16:50:37.813Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750872/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750872/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750872/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-07-11","Hospitals: Insulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment has been made of the presence of flammable cladding on hospitals; what the timetable is for assessing all hospital buildings for the presence of such cladding; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","4162"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750873","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-17","<p>The British Transport Police Authority identified savings of over 8% to be made during the period of the Spending Review from the British Transport Police’s core budgets. Any efficiency savings can potentially be reinvested into counter terrorist activities, depending on the need identified by the Chief Constable, and subject to the approval of the British Transport Police Authority.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-07-17T13:28:30.787Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750873/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750873/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750873/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-11","British Transport Police: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what his Department’s target is for efficiency savings by British Transport Police; and how he intends to allocate proceeds from that efficiency programme.","true","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","4163"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750874","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-17","<p>The current estimated total life cycle costs up to 2026/27 for the implementation and transition to the new Emergency Service Network, which will replace Airwave, is currently £78.6m. Many of the costs have been estimated on the basis of information supplied by the Home Office programme that is delivering the Emergency Services Network. The costs of implementing the Airwave replacement programme are a cost of policing the railway, to be met from the policing charges levied on rail operators for the provision of policing services.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-07-17T16:31:09.473Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750874/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750874/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750874/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-11","Emergency Services Network","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the cost of the airway replacement programme for the British Transport Police; and what additional funding his Department will provide to the British Transport Police to complete that programme.","true","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","4164"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750875","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-17","<p>In agreeing the British Transport Police Authority’s proposals for efficiency savings as part of the Spending Review, it was made clear that any savings should ensure that any material impact on the operational capability of the British Transport Police (BTP) is minimised; counter terrorist activity was exempt from the Spending Review process. The efficiency savings target includes the BTP’s core policing activities only; enhanced policing services, which are provided to operators on request on a commercial basis, are excluded from the target.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-07-17T13:20:59.663Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750875/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750875/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750875/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-11","British Transport Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what capabilities are exempt from his Department’s target for efficiency savings by the British Transport Police.","true","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","4165"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750876","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-17","<p>The Government is committed to implementing the recommendation of the Smith Commission that the functions of the British Transport Police in Scotland should be devolved. Legislative competence was devolved through the Scotland Act 2016, and a Scottish Government Bill which makes provision about the arrangements for the Police Service of Scotland to police railways and railway property has recently completed its passage through the Scottish Parliament.</p><p> </p><p>In devolving the functions, we are committed to ensuring a smooth and seamless transition which ensures effective arrangements are in place for cross-border railway policing once responsibilities have been transferred, so that we continue to have a railway policing service which works for passengers, staff and the railway.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-07-17T16:12:39.387Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750876/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750876/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750876/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-11","British Transport Police: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what his policy is on the devolution of transport policing to Scotland.","true","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","4166"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750877","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-17","<p>The Government is considering a broad range of options to optimise the protection of critical infrastructure such as nuclear sites and railways, including the future roles of the Civil Nuclear Constabulary, the Ministry of Defence Police and the British Transport Police.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-07-17T12:50:16.537Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750877/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750877/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750877/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-11","British Transport Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether it is his policy for the British Transport Police to be merged with other police forces; and if he will make a statement.","true","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","4167"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750878","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-18","<p>The Department does not generally specify staffing levels for rail franchises, as it is up to the relevant train operator to ensure it has sufficient staff in place to provide the services to which it is committed. However, the franchise agreement does contain provision limiting the amount of change in staffing levels, which can be made in the final year of the franchise without the consent of the Secretary of State.</p><p> </p><p>We aim to work with the industry, and recognise that a growing railway needs more customer-facing staff.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-07-18T13:02:22.933Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750878/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750878/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750878/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-11","Railways: Franchises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what requirements he places in franchise agreements with train-operating companies for minimum staffing levels.","false","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","4128"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750879","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-19","<p>The government is currently considering next steps in light of responses to the consultation.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-07-19T15:37:01.423Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750879/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750879/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750879/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-11","Gratuities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, when he plans to publish his response to the results of his Department's consultation on tips, gratuities, service and other charges that closed in June 2016.","false","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","4127"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750880","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-17","<p>Our Armed Forces are rightly held to the highest standards and credible, serious allegations of criminal behaviour must be investigated, in accordance with the Armed Forces Act 2006. Operation Northmoor is an independent investigation conducted by the Royal Military Police (RMP). It has discounted over 90% of the 675 allegations received because there was no evidence of a criminal or disciplinary offence. To date no case has been referred to the Service Prosecuting Authority but the investigations continue and the investigators will follow the evidence where it leads them. The RMP has full investigative independence and the Ministry of Defence has not influenced in any way the scope and duration of Operation Northmoor.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-07-17T15:42:43.343Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750880/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750880/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750880/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-11","Afghanistan: War Crimes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many cases have been opened as part of Operation Northmoor; and how many of those cases have been (a) closed and (b) remain ongoing.","false","Biography information for Will Quince","Colchester","Will Quince","4195"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750881","Home Office","false","2017-07-19","<p>The National Referral Mechanism pilot has been testing a new model for identifying and referring victims, processing cases and making effective decisions. The final stage of the evaluation is currently underway and it is anticipated that the findings will be published when that evaluation is complete.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-07-19T12:20:14.383Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750881/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750881/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750881/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-11","Slavery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when the evaluation of the pilot for a new national referral mechanism to identify and support victims of modern slavery will be published.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","4283"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750882","Home Office","false","2017-07-17","<p>The UK Government has committed to reforming the National Referral Mechanism, which is the process for identifying and supporting victims of modern slavery. Interim guidance for frontline staff has been published and we will consult with stakeholders on the statutory guidance required under section 49 of the Modern Slavery Act 2015 prior to publication.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-07-17T16:03:58.8Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750882/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750882/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750882/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-11","Slavery: Victim Support Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when guidance on victim identification and support provided for in section 49 of the Modern Slavery Act 2015 will be (a) completed and (b) published.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","4363"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750883","Home Office","false","2017-07-17","<p>The Prime Minister has made clear that one of the twelve objectives for the negotiations will be to establish a new relationship with the European Union that includes practical arrangements on matters of security and law enforcement cooperation to tackle cross-border crime and to keep our people safe.</p><p> </p><p>We continue to work closely with EU partners and we are examining the options for future cooperation arrangements once the UK has left the EU, but it would be wrong to set out unilateral positions on specific measures at this stage.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-07-17T16:10:22.907Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750883/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750883/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750883/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-11","Criminal Records: Cross Border Cooperation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking to ensure that the UK will continue to have access to the European Criminal Records Information System and Schengen Second Generation Information Services when the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","4265"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750884","Home Office","false","2017-07-17","<p>The UK continues to work with EU partners to tackle modern slavery and already has well-established rights and protections for victims of modern slavery and human trafficking, including through the National Referral Mechanism and the Modern Slavery Act 2015.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","4330","2017-07-17T16:05:42.603Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750884/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750884/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750884/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-11","Slavery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking to ensure that the rights to support for victims of modern slavery will be maintained after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","4284"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750885","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-18","<p>The Repeal Bill will ensure that the workers’ rights that are enjoyed under EU law will continue to be available in UK law after we have left the EU.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-07-18T13:47:15.5Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750885/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750885/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750885/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-11","Conditions of Employment: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the Government plans to introduce legislative proposals to transpose EU labour law into UK primary legislation.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","4331"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750886","Home Office","false","2017-07-17","<p>The UK continues to work with EU partners to tackle modern slavery and already has well-established rights and protections for victims of modern slavery and human trafficking, including through the National Referral Mechanism and the Modern Slavery Act 2015.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","4284","2017-07-17T16:05:42.713Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750886/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750886/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750886/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-11","Human Trafficking: Victim Support Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether the Government plans to bring forward legislative proposals further to protect the rights of victims of human trafficking and modern slavery as a result of the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","4330"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750887","Home Office","false","2017-07-17","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the answer given to the Hon. Member for West Bromwich East on 17th July 2017, UIN 4264.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-07-17T16:36:53.373Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750887/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750887/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750887/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-11","101 Calls: Lancashire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the average response time for answering 101 calls made to Lancashire Constabulary was in each month between 1 January 2016 and 30 June 2017.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","4341"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750888","Department of Health","false","2017-07-19","<p>Data at this level is not collected centrally.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-07-19T10:48:01.397Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750888/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750888/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750888/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-07-11","Surgical Mesh Implants: Lancashire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many transvaginal mesh implants were performed in each quarter from 1 January 2017 by (a) Lancashire Teaching Hospitals, (b) University Hospitals of Morecambe Bay, (c) Blackpool Teaching Hospitals, (d) Bolton NHS, (e) East Lancashire Hospital, (f) Southport and Ormskirk Hospitals, (g) Warrington and Halton Hospitals and (h) St Helens and Knowsley Teaching Hospitals.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","4181"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750889","Women and Equalities","false","2017-09-05","<p>No girl should be held back from reaching her potential because of her gender.</p><p>Current guidance to schools on Relationship and Sex Education encourages schools to make adequate and sensitive arrangements to help girls cope with menstruation and with requests for sanitary protection.</p><p>We have taken note of the Scottish Government’s pilot programme to provide free access to sanitary products for low-income women and female pupils and are looking for opportunities to discuss this further with them.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-09-05T08:22:51.537Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750889/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750889/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750889/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-07-11","Sanitary Protection: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what funding the Government Equalities Office plans to make available to tackle period poverty; and whether she plans to meet her equivalent in the Scottish Parliament to discuss its initiative to provide sanitary products to women and girls on low incomes.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","4361"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750890","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-13","<p>The Department does not hold information on how many people had Motability vehicles on DLA. Therefore, we are unable to collect accurate information on the number of people who have returned a Motability vehicle.</p><p> </p><p>The details of the number of people returning Motability vehicles for the requested dates and the reasons behind this are Motability’s Management Information, and the Department has no right to access this as it is an independent organisation.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-07-13T11:03:03.98Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750890/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750890/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750890/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-11","Motability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will take steps to compile information on the number of Motability vehicles which have been recalled in England between (a) January to March and (b) April to June 2017.","false","Biography information for Stephen Pound","Ealing North","Stephen Pound","4294"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750891","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-19","<p>The Apprenticeship Levy was introduced in April 2017. Therefore it is not yet possible to produce the number of employers that are paying the levy by region or parliamentary constituency. In addition, it may not be possible to publish these numbers for some geographical areas if there are only a few employers in an area, as the rules about statistical disclosure may apply if there are very small numbers.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The most recent UK wide forecasts of the number of employers paying the levy are found in the Department for Education release:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/545145/Apprenticeships_-expected_levy_and_total_spend_-_Aug_2016.pdf.</p><p> </p><p>Across the UK, this estimates that around 20,000 employers will pay the levy.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","4240","2017-07-19T14:55:03.177Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750891/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750891/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750891/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-11","Apprentices: Penistone and Stocksbridge","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the number of employers in Penistone and Stocksbridge constituency that will not be required to pay the apprenticeship levy.","false","Biography information for Angela Smith","Penistone and Stocksbridge","Angela Smith","4239"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750892","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-19","<p>The Apprenticeship Levy was introduced in April 2017. Therefore it is not yet possible to produce the number of employers that are paying the levy by region or parliamentary constituency. In addition, it may not be possible to publish these numbers for some geographical areas if there are only a few employers in an area, as the rules about statistical disclosure may apply if there are very small numbers.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The most recent UK wide forecasts of the number of employers paying the levy are found in the Department for Education release:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/545145/Apprenticeships_-expected_levy_and_total_spend_-_Aug_2016.pdf.</p><p> </p><p>Across the UK, this estimates that around 20,000 employers will pay the levy.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","4239","2017-07-19T14:55:03.387Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750892/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750892/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750892/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-11","Apprentices: Yorkshire and the Humber","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many employers will be required to pay the apprenticeship levy in (a) Penistone and Stocksbridge constituency and (b) Yorkshire and the Humber.","false","Biography information for Angela Smith","Penistone and Stocksbridge","Angela Smith","4240"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750893","Department for Education","false","2017-07-18","<p>The latest information available is for the academic year 2015/16 which is published in table 15a and 15b as part of the “A level and other 16-18 results: 2015 to 2016 (revised)” statistical first release (SFR).[1]</p><p> </p><p>[1] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/a-level-and-other-16-to-18-results-2015-to-2016-revised" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/a-level-and-other-16-to-18-results-2015-to-2016-revised</a> (“English and Maths tables: SFR05/2017” document, table 15a and 15b)</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-07-18T08:06:14.047Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750893/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750893/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750893/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-11","GCSE","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many students were required to re-sit their (a) English and (b) mathematics GCSE exams in the latest academic year for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Angela Smith","Penistone and Stocksbridge","Angela Smith","4241"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750894","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-07-19","<p>We ran a consultation between 20 December 2016 and 28 February 2017 on our proposals to ban microbeads in cosmetics and personal care products. We will publish the Government’s response to the consultation shortly.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-07-19T13:56:50.013Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750894/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750894/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750894/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-07-11","Microplastics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when he plans to publish the response to his Department’s consultation Proposals to ban the use of plastic microbeads in cosmetics and personal care products in the UK, issued on 20 December 2016.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","4334"
